title: FOIL Method
text: The F stands for First, where we multiply the first component of each terms first. $$b b$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The O stands for Outer, where we multiply the first component of the second term with the $$\frac{second}{outer}$$ component of the second term. $$6b$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The I stands for Inner, where we multiply the inner components. $$\left(-3b\right)$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The L stands for Last, where we multiply the last component of each terms. $$\left(-3\times6\right)$$

title: Simplify
text: Simplify by combining the like terms. $$(-3b$$ and 6b)
